600000322022	2020-11-04	202011	2020-11-04	Repair due to Partially Down	[  "04.11.2020 09:13:34   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..MRI_C24_600  Scanner Hardware ErrorAutomatic Shutdown !Evacuate patient immediately from the examination room !To prevent further damage, the system will be switched to Standby within 1 minute !Please contact Siemens Service immediately.CEG_SMOKEDETECTORALARMSeverity: Erroron Wed Nov 04 10:13:13 2020Original message:Computer: \\tRENMAGNVIDASource:      \\tMRI_CEG_SysLogServiceCategory: \\tNoneType:        \\tErrorEvent ID: \\t0Description:\\tMessage: Scanner Hardware ErrorAutomatic Shutdown !Evacuate patient immediately from the examination room !To prevent further damage, the system will be switched to Standby within 1 minute !Please contact Siemens Service immediately.ID: syngo.MR.MRI_CEG_NlsMessageId.Resources.CEGmsg.MRI_CEG_E_44_CEG_SMOKEDETECTORALARMSeverity: ErrorInformation: : AGYAXAAKAEEASwAfABcABwAAAAAAWgBEABIAXgBBAEMAVwA/AE0AJQAlACgAKwA9AAcAOwBaAFQAbAAvAF4ABQBIAFMABABeAA8AFABQAH0ASwBTAFkAVQBOAAMASwAPAFsAEwAWAAYAEwAPAAcARgBcAAoAQQBLAB8AFwAHAAAAAABaAEQAEgBeAE0AQABGACgAVgBiAction: : UserTimestamp: 2020-11-04T10:13:13.998+01:00Machine: RENMAGNVIDAProcess Name: C:\\\\Program Files\\\\Siemens\\\\Numaris\\\\bin\\\\ParcServicesHost.exeProcess Id: 18984AppDomain: DefaultDomainProcess Start Time: 2020-11-04T07:10:11.822+01:00Extended Properties: MsgCreateTime - 2020-11-04T10:13:13.998+01:00OriginalSeverity - ErrorCall Stack - at: syngo.MR.Utils.ErrorMessageSupport.MrSysLogItemLegacy.Logat: .MrNlsMessageIdBridgeAux.logTime first received: 2020/11/04 10:13:15Time last received: 2020/11/04 11:13:15No. of duplicates since time first received: 0Event Instructions:RSCPC Explanation:The gradient connection monitoring detected a failure within the gradient system.Action:Perform all of the following checks including UI :1. Check the gradient connections at the magnet for signs of overheating (melted or damaged insulation, discolouration)or burning smell.2. Check the temperature indicators on the cables. Is a colour change visible?3. Check the gradient connections at the RF-filter plate for signs of overheating (melted insulation) or burning smell.5. Check inside the cabinets for signs of overheating (melted insulation) or burning smell.If any damaged parts are found, please replace the damaged parts immediately. If the gradient coil is concerned,please contact HSC first.If all repairs are done successfully or if no indications for the malfunctions can be found:6. Reset the VLM device.7. Perform the following UI, depending on system type: MR28/10/S, MR29/10/S or MR30/10S (including final test with testsequence)Info:VLM: Aspirating Smoke DetectorThe monitoring device checks the gradient connections at the gradient coil, RF-filter plate and the electronic cabinets.04.11.2020 09:13:38   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2020/11/04 09:13:37 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.09.11.2020 15:40:58   Sabine Wespi ( )  *** Resolution ***unerkl?rliche PROA-\\"Leiche\\""]	11060815	175910	VIDA	MAGNETOM VIDA	MRI system triggered a smoke detector alarm, causing an automatic shutdown and patient evacuation	No troubleshooting steps were recorded	No corrective action was taken	Environmental Interference	Environment	202011	CH	Switzerland	2020-11-09	N	VA50A-SP01	110
