508100952889	2024-09-18	202409	2024-09-18	Repair due to Partially Down	[  "18.09.2024 08:08:51  -3 RFC_HC_SOC RFC_HC_SOC (RFC_HC_SOC)Endere?o do Equipamento: DONA ADMA JAFET 91Descri??o do Problema e/ou Informa??es Adicionais: Customer and the Application Team reports that the head spectroscopy results diverges from N4 based system to NX based system, with the same patient.\\nMyoinositol results are discrepant between software versions and, in case of NX_based-system, above the literature reference values.\\nThis is compromising the diagnosis.\\nBecause of that, the customer has suspended spectroscopy studies on our NX-based-equipment.\\n\\nIs the system working as specified? Or is there any software issue?\\nWhat has been changed in the software and why? How to read the results?\\nCustomer requests a response explaining the difference between the versions, whether there is a way to obtain the values as they were previously or if any conversion is necessary (how to read the results).Telefone do Solicitante: 11 970705291;Chamado aberto por:  33090146 WAGNER NESPOLI ZANATTA18.09.2024 08:49:16  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/18 08:49:08 Felipe Vital Fialho Phone|The escalated Call has generated the following Ticket number|: PEAK5540779|19.09.2024 08:35:02  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 11:34:51 ALAN RIBAS OLIVEIRA DA SILVA Phone +55 7|1 3114-1911|The escalated Call has generated the following Ticket number|: PEAK5540779|19.09.2024 08:40:32  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 11:40:22 ALAN RIBAS OLIVEIRA DA SILVA Phone +55 7|1 3114-1911|PEAK Incident is Potential Safety Issue.19.09.2024 08:41:18  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 11:41:08 SEQURE Interface User Phone|Complaint 2024-00069567 is created.19.09.2024 08:59:11  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 11:59:01 ALAN RIBAS OLIVEIRA DA SILVA Phone +55 7|1 3114-1911|ST00103756| Request for Escalation to HSC:| Dear HSC Team.||Could you please handle this new escalation for the Spectros|copy results N4 X NX?|It's the same as PEAK5494747/PEAK5471846.|Due to the nature of the supposed failure, and the fact that| the customer has stopped the spectroscopy studies in the NX|-based-systems, I've opened a complaint during the &quot;Saf|ety Assessment&quot; before routing it to you.||Best regards,||Alan Ribas19.09.2024 09:17:35  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 02:17:23 Stefan Weber Phone +49 (9131) 84-2613|PPI opened by HSC|Cause Analysis|The MRS post-processing algorithm in NumarisX is different f|rom that in Numaris4. Therefore, we cannot directly compare|the results between them. Moreover, for the spectral quantif|ication, we don't compare the results from two different pos|t-processing tools because there're many factors to alter th|e values.||Behavior described in SKB0015083|-&gt; https://skb.siemens-healthineers.com/Pages/SKBAdvanced|ViewKBDocument.aspx?docid=SKB001508319.09.2024 09:17:37  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 02:17:27 Stefan Weber Phone +49 (9131) 84-2613|Incident has been linked to problem SOL0001212619.09.2024 10:07:43  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 03:07:33 Stefan Weber Phone +49 (9131) 84-2613||************************************************************|*********************|HSC PRIMARILY ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS:|The MRS post-processing algorithm in NumarisX is different f|rom that in Numaris4. Therefore, we cannot directly compare|the results between them. Moreover, for the spectral quantif|ication, we don't compare the results from two different pos|t-processing tools because there're many factors to alter th|e values.||There're several factors affecting the quantification result|s:||- The model of the metabolite basis (single-peak only or mul|tiplets)|--&gt; In Numaris4, only single resonance peak is possible t|o configure the basis. If a metabolite has several resonance| frequencies, we have to configure them separately. Therefor|e, the integral value of the metabolite comes from only one|of the resonance frequencies, and the information it not com|plete.|--&gt; In NumarisX, multiplets are used. For the metabolites| have several resonance frequencies, it's possible to calcul|ate the integral value under different resonance frequencies| together. Thus, the integral values are usually larger.||- Different preprocessing steps/algorithm:|--&gt; The signal fitting domain:|---&gt; In Numaris4 we fit the signal in frequency domain an|d in NumarisX it's done in time domain.|---&gt; As a result, the phase correction would not affect t|he quantification values anymore in NumarisX.|--&gt; Water referencing:|---&gt; In Numaris4 by default we use Lowpass filter, and in| NumarisX the SVD is used as default.||Please find the details in User Manual:|- Operator Manual – syngo.MR Spectroscopy|- Addendum – syngo.MR Spectroscopy||If the customer has some old spectral data acquired in Numar|is4 and wants to compare with the results analyzed from the|new MR Spectro post-processing tool in NumarisX, the workaro|und would be recalculating the old data in NumarisX again. T|hen it's more reasonable to compare the results calculated f|rom the same post-processing tool. The SKB0015083 (https://s|kb.siemens-healthineers.com/Pages/SKBAdvancedViewKBDocument.|aspx?docid=SKB0015083) describes the information with more d|etails.|||INTERIM SOLUTION:|The conclusion is &quot;system works as specified&quot;.|Workaround: if the customer wants to compare the old data in| Numaris4 and new data in NumarisX, please recalculate the o|ld data in NumarisX and then the result would be comparable.|||------------------------------------------------------------|----------|The request was forwarded to the BL.|As soon as new information is available the incident / probl|em / SKB-Entry will be updated accordingly.|For further requests/feedback/information please contact the| DCU   directly and| refer to SOL00012126|------------------------------------------------------------|-----------||************************************************************|*********************19.09.2024 10:46:23  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/19 01:46:12 ALAN RIBAS OLIVEIRA DA SILVA Phone +55 7|1 3114-1911|||From: Siemens Healthineers RG BR RSC MR TSE &lt;rgbrrscmrtse| &gt;|Sent: Thursday, September 19, 2024 10:45 AM|To: NESPOLI ZANATTA, WAGNER &lt;wagner.zanatta@siemens-healt|hineers.com&gt;; Siemens Healthineers RG BR RSC MR TSE &lt;r| &gt;|Subject: PEAK5540779/PEAK5540775/PEAK5540774/PEAK5540768 - R|E: Spectroscopy results are not reliable -  6 - 50|8100952887 -  8 -  9 - Hospital Sirio Li|banes||Dear Zanatta.||Thanks for contacting the RSC.||I have opened a PSI and a ST with the HSC for the following|tickets.|| 9/PEAK5540779 – Complaint 2024-00069567/ HSC ST00|103756| 8/PEAK5540775 – Complaint 2024-00069572/ HSC ST00|103769| 7/PEAK5540774 – Complaint 2024-00069577/ HSC ST00|103776| 6/PEAK5540768 – Complaint 2024-00069579 / HSC ST0|0103779||For each ticket, please stick to the current response the Or|ganization has so far, which is:||The MRS post-processing algorithm in NumarisX is different f|rom that in Numaris4.|Therefore, we cannot directly compare the results between th|em.|Moreover, for the spectral quantification, we don't compare|the results from two different post-processing tools because| there're many factors to alter the values.||Behavior described in SKB0015083|-&gt; https://skb.siemens-healthineers.com/Pages/SKBAdvanced|ViewKBDocument.aspx?docid=SKB0015083|||More detail:|||____________INITIAL ANALYSIS_____________||The MRS post-processing algorithm in NumarisX is different f|rom that in Numaris4. Therefore, we cannot directly compare|the results between them. Moreover, for the spectral quantif|ication, we don't compare the results from two different pos|t-processing tools because there're many factors to alter th|e values.||There're several factors affecting the quantification result|s:||- The model of the metabolite basis (single-peak only or mul|tiplets)|--&gt; In Numaris4, only single resonance peak is possible t|o configure the basis. If a metabolite has several resonance| frequencies, we have to configure them separately. Therefor|e, the integral value of the metabolite comes from only one|of the resonance frequencies, and the information it not com|plete.|--&gt; In NumarisX, multiplets are used. For the metabolites| have several resonance frequencies, it's possible to calcul|ate the integral value under different resonance frequencies| together. Thus, the integral values are usually larger.||- Different preprocessing steps/algorithm:|--&gt; The signal fitting domain:|---&gt; In Numaris4 we fit the signal in frequency domain an|d in NumarisX it's done in time domain.|---&gt; As a result, the phase correction would not affect t|he quantification values anymore in NumarisX.|--&gt; Water referencing:|---&gt; In Numaris4 by default we use Lowpass filter, and in| NumarisX the SVD is used as default.||Please find the details in User Manual:|- Operator Manual – syngo.MR Spectroscopy|- Addendum – syngo.MR Spectroscopy||If the customer has some old spectral data acquired in Numar|is4 and wants to compare with the results analyzed from the|new MR Spectro post-processing tool in NumarisX, the workaro|und would be recalculating the old data in NumarisX again. T|hen it's more reasonable to compare the results calculated f|rom the same post-processing tool. The SKB0015083 (https://s|kb.siemens-healthineers.com/Pages/SKBAdvancedViewKBDocument.|aspx?docid=SKB0015083&amp;sid=d0ae8516-2470-4f72-a2ee-df6ee4|048f3a&amp;ix=1&amp;viewLastPublished=True) describes the in|formation with more details.||_____________ACTION PLAN_____________||Please provide the above information to customer.||The conclusion is &quot;system works as specified&quot;.|Workaround: if the customer wants to compare the old data in| Numaris4 and new data in NumarisX, please recalculate the o|ld data in NumarisX and then the result would be comparable.|||Anyway, each ticket was linked to the already existing Probl|em Ticket SOL00012126.||So, please follow the HSC/DCU feedback above to work on with| the customer.|As soon as new information is available the incident / probl|em / SKB-Entry will be updated accordingly.|You can follow up the issue with the DCU directly (mr-compla| referring &amp; dcusupport.| ) referring to the respective t|ickets and complaint numbers above, as well as the common pr|oblem ticket SOL00012126.||Best regards,||Alan Ribas|20.09.2024 06:13:06  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/09/20 09:12:52 SEQURE Interface User Phone|The complaint was reviewed by DCU: Magnetic Resonance Erlang|en (DI MR ERL)||Comment by reviewer:|Your complaint has been received and assessed by MR DCU and|will be forwarded to the appropriate department for investig|ation. We may contact you if additional information (CC-part|s, savelog, etc.) is needed.||For immediate technical support please contact your local cu|stomer service support team first. You will be informed when| the investigation has been completed.||Posted by: Raj Rani (EXT) ( )17.12.2024 16:42:34  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/12/17 04:42:33 Wagner Nespoli Zanatta Phone +55 11 3908|-2258|Há suposta reuni?o a ser marcada com clientes pelo HSC - Agu|ardando23.12.2024 08:56:33  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2024/12/23 11:56:32 Almir Rodrigues Tavares Phone +55 11 390|8-1665|Chamado analisado pelo Zanata19.02.2025 05:30:16  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2025/02/19 08:30:14 SEQURE Interface User Phone|Rationale for Not Safety classification: 2025-02-13 PSI &gt;| PPI // Non Safety Rationale|Per the report there was no injury associated with this issu|e. It was stated that Spectroscopy results are not comparabl|e between syngo classic and syngo.via. The described issue i|s currently not a specified function of our system. Therefor|e, we will not classify and process this request as a compla|int but as a customer wish.|However, a workaround has already been provided to have comp|areable results.|---|2024-09-20 PSI:|Per the complaint report there was no injury associated with| this issue. It was stated that result values are not compar|able between syngo classic and syngo.via. According to the r|isk assessment 7139020-EGA-504-01 (misdiagnosis), wrong diag|nosis is consistently defined as a potential harm with a Sev|erity of S=2. Therefore, in case of reoccurrence a death or|serious injury is very unlikely.||Posted by: Anna-Carolina Eckl ( )19.02.2025 05:35:51  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2025/02/19 08:35:49 SEQURE Interface User Phone|Complaint Closure Summary:|Thank you for your input regarding our MR medical device. We| would like to inform you that your input has been received|and assessed. Per the complaint report there was no injury o|r misdiagnosis associated with this issue. It was stated in|the complaint ticket that the MR Spectroscopy results are no|t comparable between syngo.classic (Numaris/4) and syngo.via| (Numaris/X).||ROOT CAUSE:|Our experts investigated the complained issue based on the p|rovided information and confirmed the observed behavior.||The investigation has shown that the results from syngo.clas|sic (Numaris/4) and syngo.via (or Numaris/X) are not compara|ble due to different algorithms. Different post-processing p|rocedures are used on syngo.MR Spectroscopy (syngo.via) and|the Spectroscopy taskcard (syngo.classic).|Therefore, integral values from the two algorithms cannot be| compared directly.|| Additionally for the spectral quantification, there are sev|eral factors affecting the results:|?  The model of the metabolite basis (single-peak only or mu|ltiplets)|--&gt; In Numaris/4, only single resonance peak is possible|to configure the basis. If a metabolite has several resonanc|e frequencies, they have to be configured separately. Theref|ore, the integral value of the metabolite comes from only on|e of the resonance frequencies, and the information it not c|omplete.|--&gt; In Numaris/X, multiplets are used. For the metabolite|s have several resonance frequencies, it's possible to calcu|late the integral value under different resonance frequencie|s together. Thus, the integral values are usually larger.|| Furthermore, as mentioned before, different preprocessing a|lgorithms are used.|?  The signal fitting domain:|---&gt; In Numaris/4, the signal is fitted in frequency doma|in and in Numaris/X it's done in time domain. As a result, t|he phase correction would not affect the quantification valu|es anymore in Numaris/X.|?  Water referencing:|--&gt; In Numaris/4 by default Lowpass filter are used, and|in Numaris/X the SVD is used as default.||For more details, please consult the user manuals and check|SKB0015083:|- Operator Manual – syngo.MR Spectroscopy|- Addendum – syngo.MR Spectroscopy||As a possible workaround to this issue our experts recommend| recalculating the old spectral data in Numaris/X. Then the|spectral data acquired in Numaris/4 and Numaris/X at least u|se the same post-processing tool to get the results. These v|alues could be compared.|Since no software error was detected, nothing will be change|d within our implementation. Our system works as expected an|d specified.||INTERIM SOLUTION:|As a possible workaround to this issue our experts recommend| recalculating the old spectral data in Numaris/X. Then the|spectral data acquired in Numaris/4 and Numaris/X at least u|se the same post-processing tool to get the results. These v|alues could be compared.||SOLUTION:|n.a.||STATEMENT WHETHER THE DEVICE FAILED TO MEET ITS SPECIFICATIO|N:|No||Attachments sent: 0||Posted by: Anna-Carolina Eckl ( )19.02.2025 05:35:54  -3 Interface SHS PEAK (RFC_PEAK)|2025/02/19 08:35:53 SEQURE Interface User Phone|Complaint Closure Summary:|Thank you for your input regarding our MR medical device. We| would like to inform you that your input has been received|and assessed. Per the complaint report there was no injury o|r misdiagnosis associated with this is