P Target 'SRS_ftp'          * Send When: 'at once'For NumarisX systems (Windows10):     Data transfer follows 2 possible ways, since none works in your case, you have to check both:     The MR system is transferring the data via AutoReportsIB_Sample/IB_Transfer and/or qdb, so be sure that these AutoReports are set up and activated correctly          * Check under &quot;Technical Configuration&quot;-&gt; &quot;Remote Service&quot; that all Auto Reports are activated          * manually transfer all files C:\\\\ProgramData\\\\Siemens\\\\Numaris\\\\MriExchange\\\\QADB\\\\Export*.xml and verify the reception at the cRSP under &quot;Files Download&quot;          * if no files show up, fix the connectivity     Additionally, the CAN24 is sending magnet data daily, so verify that as well          * connect to the CAN24 of this system via remote          * select &quot;Test Message Transfer&quot; and click &quot;submit&quot;          * within minutes, you should see a file (e.g. MR*****_T DATA_20200924_115746) transferred to the cRSP under&quot;Files Download&quot;          * if no files show up, fix the connectivity”16.04.2022 03:11:51   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2022/04/16 03:11:50 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.11.05.2022 09:08:06   Florian Koerner ( )  Die Anlage sendet wieder Daten.*** Resolution ***: * 11.05.2022 09:08:30   Florian Koerner ( )Ticket wurde aus administrativen Gründen geschlossen.11.05.2022 09:10:04   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0004/HQCO2022/05/11 09:09:57 PK SAP Country Integration User  Phone*** Resolution **** 11.05.2022 09:09:51   Florian Koerner ( )  CRM FOR TASK 0002 2022-05-11 11:08:32 CSE K?rner FlorianShort text: FOR TASK 0002Long text:*** Resolution ***: * 11.05.2022 09:08:30   Florian Koerner ( )Ticket wurde aus administrativen Gründen geschlossen.RSC final safety assessment result NNN"]	10838610	174768	AMIRA	MAGNETOM AMIRA	MRI system stopped sending QDB AutoRepo