tions inside the compressor. 3: IFP version:  3.1: Remove the cover of the compressor.  3.2: Perform a leak check at the connections inside the compressor. 4: Repair the leakage 5: Charge the refrigerator system with Helium gas (99.999%purity). Refer to TSG. Static pressure:  ST-7H : 16.0 to 16.5 bar for 50/60 Hz  F70: 13.5 to 14 bar for 50/60Hz  CSW 71: 16.5 to 17 bar for 50/60HzST-7H (Magnetom Sola, Vida): 16.0 -16.5 bar for 50/60Hz  Perform a Static Pressure Test via Diagnose / Magnet&amp;Cooling / Compressor StatusInfo:Early warning. Expected reduction of cooling power. System still operational.04.01.2021 15:36:19   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2021/01/04 03:36:18 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.04.01.2021 16:09:12   Miroslav Vacek ( )  *** Resolution ***: * 04.01.2021 16:09:17   Miroslav Vacek ( )Magnet quality Page kontrolliert, OK"]	11060815	175711	VIDA	MAGNETOM VIDA	Helium leakage detected in the refrigeration circuit, potentially causing increased helium boil-off and 50K shield temperature rise	No troubleshooting steps were recorded	Magnet quality was checked and confirmed to be OK	Helium Level and Loss	Magnet	202101	CH	Switzerland	2021-01-04	N	VA50A-SP01	110
