600000698746	2022-04-28	202204	2022-04-29	Repair due to Partially Down	[  "28.04.2022 03:20:16   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..Mon_MIS - This site (CH) stopped sending the QDB AutoReport. on Thu Apr 28 05:19:02 2022Original message:Node:          MR11410481-202007Message group:Application:   MED_MR_HeMonObject:        EMEASeverity:      MinorText:          Mon_MIS - This site (CH) stopped sending theQDB AutoReport.Time first received: 2022/04/28 05:19:04Time last received: 2022/04/28 07:19:04No. of duplicates since time first received: 0Event Instructions:Explanation:     The system is not sending MR Quality data.     The general connectivity is no longer given or the AutoReport parameters are set wrong.Action:     Connect to system via Remote, analyze the Eventlog of the CustomerLog section for Transfermanager errors (e.g. FTPpassword)For Numaris4 system (Windows XP/7):     Try manual transfer of data, if it fails, arrange fix (Configuration on site or line check by the SRS Helpdesk)     Transfer all pending data from the directory C:\\\\MedCom\\\\service\\\\@work\\\\output by multi-selecting pending *Export*.xml and *.exp files (shift-click) up to 50 files at once and click 'Go'.     Do not select more files for one transfer as it will fail. Repeat until all missing files are transferred.     Deactivate the file compression where available, else the manual transfer will not succeed entirely. Only uncompressed file transfer will remove the files locally after a successful transmission.     Check AutoReport 'QDB' for these parameters:          * must be enabled          * Start Date: before today          * End Date: set to maximum          * File: path must be C:\\\\MedCom\\\\service\\\\html\\\\seso\\\\sitedb\\\\export\\\\*export.xml          * Mode: 'Time Triggered'          * Sample When: set multiple trigger times by setting Sampling to 'Contiuously' and selecting 02:20;08:05;09:45          * Send What: 'as separate file(s) without mail' and FTP Target 'SRS_ftp'          * Send When: 'at once'For NumarisX systems (Windows10):     Data transfer follows 2 possible ways, since none works in your case, you have to check both:     The MR system is transferring the data via AutoReportsIB_Sample/IB_Transfer and/or qdb, so be sure that these AutoReports are set up and activated correctly          * Check under &quot;Technical Configuration&quot;-&gt; &quot;Remote Service&quot; that all Auto Reports are activated          * manually transfer all files C:\\\\ProgramData\\\\Siemens\\\\Numaris\\\\MriExchange\\\\QADB\\\\Export*.xml and verify the reception at the cRSP under &quot;Files Download&quot;          * if no files show up, fix the connectivity     Additionally, the CAN24 is sending magnet data daily, so verify that as well          * connect to the CAN24 of this system via remote          * select &quot;Test Message Transfer&quot; and click &quot;submit&quot;          * within minutes, you should see a file (e.g. MR*****_T DATA_20200924_115746) transferred to the cRSP under&quot;Files Download&quot;          * if no files show up, fix the connectivity”28.04.2022 03:20:22   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2022/04/28 03:20:20 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.28.04.2022 06:53:55   Alexis Francisco Lemus ( )***#Resolution Provided#***Disp.29.04.2022 15:12:02   Rainer Berger ( )  <<<<<<<<< REPORTTEXT >>>>>>>>>> by Rainer BERGER*** Action Taken ***:Berger RainerProAktiv Meldung: CAN24 sendet nicht- Kontrolle in Datenbank: Seit dem 18.4.2022 wurden keine Daten mehr vomMR gesendet- tel. Besprechung mit Hr. Abdullahu: Er hat die CAN24 über F41geresetetAm Montag wird kontrolliert, ob wieder Daten gesendet werden<<<<<<<<< TROUBLETEXT >>>>>>>>> by Rainer BERGERCAN24 testen<<<<<<<<< REPORT-CODES >>>>>>>>>29.04.2022 15:12:15   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0012/HQCO2022/04/29 03:12:11 PK SAP Country Integration User  Phone*** Resolution **** 29.04.2022 