600000700019	2022-04-29	202205	2022-05-05	Scheduled Reactive Service	[  "29.04.2022 09:11:14   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..Mon_RET - The Primary/Secondary water circuit of MR175039 in DE is losing pressure. (Critical Return Pressure reached in 19.0 days) on Fri Apr 29 11:09:29 2022Original message:Node:          MR10838610-175039Message group:Application:   MED_MR_HeMonObject:        EMEASeverity:      MajorText:          Mon_RET : The Primary/Secondary water circuit of MR175039 in DE is losing pressure. (Critical Return Pressure reached in 19.0 days)Time first received: 2022/04/29 11:09:32Time last received: 2022/04/29 13:09:32No. of duplicates since time first received: 0Event Instructions:Explanation: The primary/secondary water circuit of the SEP/IFP/ACS/COO is losing water.Consequence:1. Insufficient water pressure.2. Water pump will stop soon.3. Scanning will be stopped.4. Helium compressor will be stopped.5. Magnet will lose Helium.Action: Systems without auto refill device:1. Refill water.2. Check if the ball valve of expansion vessel is open.3. Check for leakage.Systems with auto refill device:1. Refill the auto refill device: Pressure should be between 4 - 6bar.    Refer to TSG / Cooling / Filling the auto_refill device2. Monitor the return pressure via SeSo. Water circuit should be filled from the auto refill device.3. Return pressure should increase to about 1.0bar.4. Re-charge the auto refill device: Pressure should be between 4 - 6bar.5. If no re-charging from the auto refill device:    Check the pressure regulator setting of the auto refilldevice (default setting is 1.0 bar)    Re-adjust the pressure regulator of the auto refill device.29.04.2022 09:11:23   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2022/04/29 09:11:19 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.29.04.2022 09:38:50   Florian Koerner ( )  @Disp:Proaktive MeldungNicht mit dem Kunden gesprochen.RP bei 0,73bar. Hier sollte innerhalb zwei 