ation versionor release date yet as the implementation is still in the planning st\\tage.We regret any inconveniences caused by this issue.INTERIM SOLUTION:If this issue reoccurs, the user needs to restart MR View&amp;GO.SOLUTION:n.a.STATEMENT WHETHER THE DEVICE FAILED TO MEET ITS SPECIFICATION:YesDecision by: CCB MRDecision date: 2022/08/22 00:00:0024.10.2022 11:27:07   (MEDINVL)  0022/HQPM2022/10/24 13:27:05  Phone2022/10/24 13:26:51 - SCHUMACHER, RUTH-MARIA - Sent to IM: Yes # Sent to Country: Yes # Send interim solution:please check also SKB0132768Thank you for your input regarding our MR medical device. We would like to inform you that your input has been receivedand asses\\tsed. Per the complaint it was stated that in MR View&amp;GOan error message occurred during data load with cardiac images.ROOT CAUSE:Our experts investigated the complained issue based on the provided information. Here, an exception was determined which occurs d\\turing opening MR View&amp;GO when using the “create2D Stack” or “Create 4D stack” feature before closing on the same patient.\\t Here, the data is not loading properly, and an error message is popping up.If this issue reoccurs, the user needs to restart MR View&amp;GO.Our experts agree that this behavior should be improved. Unfortunately, it was decided that this issue cannot be fixed within Num\\taris X_VA50A anymore. Nevertheless, our experts are currently evaluating a possible solution to this issue for future software ve\\trsions. Unfortunately, we cannot name a realization versionor release date yet as the implementation is still in the planning st\\tage.We regret any inconveniences caused by this issue.INTERIM SOLUTION:If this issue reoccurs, the user needs to restart MR View&amp;GO.SOLUTION:n.a.STATEMENT WHETHER THE DEVICE FAILED TO MEET ITS SPECIFICATION:Yes02.11.2022 11:55:01   (MEDINVL)  0023/RESP2022/11/02 12:54:53 Juri Helfrich Phone +49 (9131) 6825528deselected : PM Action Required10.11.2022 09:41:32   (MEDINVL)  0024