600000369889	2021-02-02	202102	2021-02-02	Repair due to Partially Down	[  "02.02.2021 14:29:33   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..Mon_RET - The Primary/Secondary water circuit of MR176014 in NL is losing pressure. (Critical Return Pressure reached in 5.0 days) on Tue Feb 02 15:21:50 2021Original message:Node:          MR11060815-176014Message group:Application:   MED_MR_HeMonObject:        EMEASeverity:      MajorText:          Mon_RET : The Primary/Secondary water circuit of MR176014 in NL is losing pressure. (Critical Return Pressure reached in 5.0 days)Time first received: 2021/02/02 15:21:54Time last received: 2021/02/02 16:21:54No. of duplicates since time first received: 0Event Instructions:Explanation: The primary/secondary water circuit of the SEP/IFP/ACS/COO is losing water.Consequence:1. Insufficient water pressure.2. Water pump will stop soon.3. Scanning will be stopped.4. Helium compressor will be stopped.5. Magnet will lose Helium.Action: Systems without auto refill device:1. Refill water.2. Check if the ball valve of expansion vessel is open.3. Check for leakage.Systems with auto refill device:1. Refill the auto refill device: Pressure should be between 4 - 6bar.    Refer to TSG / Cooling / Filling the auto_refill device2. Monitor the return pressure via SeSo. Water circuit should be filled from the auto refill device.3. Return pressure should increase to about 1.0bar.4. Re-charge the auto refill device: Pressure should be between 4 - 6bar.5. If no re-charging from the auto refill device:    Check the pressure regulator setting of the auto refilldevice (default setting is 1.0 bar)    Re-adjust the pressure regulator of the auto refill device.02.02.2021 14:29:38   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2021/02/02 02:29:38 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.02.02.2021 15:30:17   Bianca Oude Hesselink ( )Please schedule a refill of the secundary water cooling system. 1h ofwork.* 03.02.2021 06:25:0