600002101717	2023-11-17	202311	2023-11-23	Repair due to Partially Down	[  "17.11.2023 20:02:04   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..Mon_RET - The secondary water circuit of MR181701 in FR is losing pressure. (Critical Return Pressure reached in 20 days) on Fri Nov 17 20:58:24 2023Original message:Node:          MR10840816-181701Message group:Application:   MED_MR_HeMonObject:        EMEASeverity:      MajorText:          Mon_RET : The secondary water circuit of MR181701 in FR is losing pressure. (Critical Return Pressure reached in 20 days)Time first received: 2023/11/17 20:58:31Time last received: 2023/11/17 21:58:31No. of duplicates since time first received: 0Event Instructions:Explanation: The primary/secondary water circuit of the SEP/IFP/ACS/COO is losing water.Consequence:1. Insufficient water pressure.2. Water pump will stop soon.3. Scanning will be stopped.4. Helium compressor will be stopped.5. Magnet will lose Helium.Action: Systems without auto refill device:1. Refill water.2. Check if the ball valve of expansion vessel is open.3. Check for leakage.Systems with auto refill device:1. Refill the auto refill device: Pressure should be between 4 - 6bar.    Refer to TSG / Cooling / Filling the auto_refill device2. Monitor the return pressure via SeSo. Water circuit should be filled from the auto refill device.3. Return pressure should increase to about 1.0bar.4. Re-charge the auto refill device: Pressure should be between 4 - 6bar.5. If no re-charging from the auto refill device:    Check the pressure regulator setting of the auto refilldevice (default setting is 1.0 bar)    Re-adjust the pressure regulator of the auto refill device.17.11.2023 20:02:15   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2023/11/17 08:02:13 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.20.11.2023 14:09:07   Anthony Gautier ( )baisse très lente de la pression du circuit d'eau secondairepression à 0,76b# Plan d'action : remettre en pression le 