600002101773	2023-11-17	202311	2023-11-18	Repair due to Partially Down	[  "17.11.2023 23:13:56   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..MRI_C24_RampUpfail - * switch heater fault on Sat Nov 18 00:11:23 2023Original message:Node:          MR11408426-207014Message group:Application:   MED_MR_CANObject:        EMEASeverity:      WarningText:          MRI_C24_810 : * switch heater faultTime first received: 2023/11/18 00:11:24Time last received: 2023/11/18 01:11:24No. of duplicates since time first received: 0Event Instructions:Explanation:Scanning is not possibleThe following reasons can cause this problem:1.) Operational failure of the switch heater was detected.2.) The UPS signals indicate it is in an alarm condition.3.) MPS Cable test current limit exceeded (MPS error 7)4.) Ramp up attempt failed because RDL Rundownload test sequence was unsuccessful.5.) MPS operation inhibited due to RDL temperature is out of range.Action:Remotely1.) Check Heater, RundownLoad and MiniUPS values in Magnet&amp;Cooling/Magnet Status2.) Check all cooling values in Magnet&amp;Cooling/Cooling Status3.) Download the related logfiles in Magnet&amp;Cooling/Magnet Status for further investigation.4.) Download the MSCU logs (RDL test, MPS Self Test, RampUp) in Repair/Magnet Ramping for further investigation.Onsite1.) Check the cabling at the MSCU and give it a reset.2.) Check the function and the LEDs status of the MiniUPS devices (Powersupply and controller) in the EPC.3.) Check the temperature sensor on top of the run down load in the magnet room.4.) Re-Run the MPS selftest in Magnet&amp;Cooling/MagnetRampSetupFurther actions to be determined with RSC and/or Magnet HSC.17.11.2023 23:14:08   I. Siemens Healthineers (MEDINVL) Phone 1522/2..0001/PROA2023/11/17 11:14:06 PK GSMS Integration User  PhoneProactive Notification posted.20.11.2023 10:37:04   V. Correia De Lacerda Begonha ( ) Phone..0003/HQUPSee notification number  223.01.2024 18:33:08   B. Soares Miranda ( )  *** Resolution *